{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3288702,"name":"Cadel","username":"Cadel","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/59ef9b/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-01-19T03:54:09.185Z","cooked":"<p>My team is trying to use SRX Mag Encoders as absolute encoders. Preferably I would like to use the data port on the Spark Max, <a href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/srx-mag-encoder-with-spark-max/422875">here</a> team 4739 show how to wire the SRX Mag Encoder for absolute position but I am still very confused if this will work if the Spark Max is in brushless mode.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2024-01-19T03:54:09.185Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":140,"reads":114,"readers_count":113,"score":717.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":450992,"topic_slug":"ctre-srx-mag-absolute-encoder-using-spark-max-data-port","display_username":"Cadel","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/srx-mag-encoder-with-spark-max/422875","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"SRX Mag encoder with Spark Max","clicks":31}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63349,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2023"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-srx-mag-absolute-encoder-using-spark-max-data-port/450992/1","custom_user_title":"2023","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3289205,"name":"Aaron Huang","username":"AaronHuang","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/779978/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-01-19T18:36:33.772Z","cooked":"<p>You can take a look at the <a href="https://docs.revrobotics.com/sparkmax/operating-modes/using-encoders/alternate-encoder-mode" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Alternate Encoder Mode</a> Page on the Rev docs. It should work after some config.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2024-01-19T18:36:33.772Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":79,"readers_count":78,"score":30.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":450992,"topic_slug":"ctre-srx-mag-absolute-encoder-using-spark-max-data-port","display_username":"Aaron Huang","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.revrobotics.com/sparkmax/operating-modes/using-encoders/alternate-encoder-mode","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Alternate Encoder Mode - SPARK MAX","clicks":18}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53779,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Some random"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-srx-mag-absolute-encoder-using-spark-max-data-port/450992/2","custom_user_title":"Some random","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3289248,"name":"guineawheek","username":"guineawheek","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/guineawheek/{size}/180797_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-19T18:55:44.703Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="AaronHuang" data-post="2" data-topic="450992">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/779978/48.png" class="avatar"> AaronHuang:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>You can take a look at the <a href="https://docs.revrobotics.com/sparkmax/operating-modes/using-encoders/alternate-encoder-mode" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Alternate Encoder Mode</a></p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>Despite the naming, alternate encoder mode is only used for using quadrature signals with brushless motors. For absolute position you want to use the <code>SparkAbsoluteEncoder</code> class and <code>getAbsoluteEncoder</code> function, as the SRX Mag outputs a <span class="abbreviation">PWM<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Pulse Width Modulation"></template></span> “duty cycle” signal to measure absolute position.</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">// (adapted from https://docs.reduxrobotics.com/canandcoder/spark-max#code-example-java)
//
// Instantiate a Spark MAX and get a handle to a PWM absolute encoder
CANSparkMax sparkmax = new CANSparkMax(0, MotorType.kBrushed);
var sparkencoder = sparkmax.getAbsoluteEncoder(SparkMaxAbsoluteEncoder.Type.kDutyCycle);

// Change this as needed, 8 points to average for velocity measurement is a
// decent starting point
sparkencoder.setAverageDepth(8);

// Reads the absolute position in rotations
sparkencoder.getPosition();

// configure the Spark Max to use the PWM-connected encoder for
// closed-loop control
sparkmax.getPIDController().setFeedbackDevice(sparkencoder);

// Additionally, SparkMaxPIDController.setPositionPIDWrappingEnabled() and
// similar functions may be useful for swerve pivot applications.
</code></pre>
<p>See also: <a href="https://codedocs.revrobotics.com/java/com/revrobotics/sparkabsoluteencoder" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">SparkAbsoluteEncoder (FRC-REVLib API)</a></p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":6,"updated_at":"2024-01-19T18:56:13.498Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":11,"reads":74,"readers_count":73,"score":74.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":450992,"topic_slug":"ctre-srx-mag-absolute-encoder-using-spark-max-data-port","display_username":"guineawheek","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://codedocs.revrobotics.com/java/com/revrobotics/sparkabsoluteencoder","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"SparkAbsoluteEncoder (FRC-REVLib API)","clicks":10}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":31855,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"software @ redux robotics"},"post_url":"/t/ctre-srx-mag-absolute-encoder-using-spark-max-data-port/450992/3","custom_user_title":"software @ redux robotics","reactions":[{"id":"point_up","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3289582,"name":"Cadel","username":"Cadel","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/59ef9b/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-01-20T00:59:06.454Z","cooked":"<p>I tried this today with the standard ribbon cable and I couldn’t get it to work, is there any rewiring I need to do